@startuml fig-A06-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title NAT and DHCP — E2 PCAP Flow (DORA + NAT Rewrite)

participant "h1\n(client)" as C #FFE0B2
participant "h3\n(gateway)\nDHCP + NAT" as GW #E1BEE7
participant "h4\n(external\nserver)" as SRV #C8E6C9
participant "tcpdump\n(gateway\ninterface any)" as CAP #ECEFF1

== DHCP — DORA SEQUENCE ==

C -[#1565C0]> GW : DHCP Discover\n(broadcast, xid=0x1234)
note right of CAP : R1: bootp.option.dhcp==1 >= 1
GW -[#43A047]-> C : DHCP Offer\n(10.0.1.10, lease=600s, gw=10.0.1.1)
note right of CAP : R2: bootp.option.dhcp==2 >= 1
C -[#1565C0]> GW : DHCP Request\n(requesting 10.0.1.10)
note right of CAP : R3: bootp.option.dhcp==3 >= 1
GW -[#43A047]-> C : DHCP Ack\n(confirmed 10.0.1.10)
note right of CAP : R4: bootp.option.dhcp==5 >= 1

== NAT — OUTBOUND ACCESS ==

C -> GW : HTTP GET h4:80\nsrc=10.0.1.10
note left of GW : internal capture:\nsrc = 10.0.1.10
GW -> SRV : HTTP GET h4:80\nsrc=192.168.1.1 (MASQUERADE)
note right of GW : external capture:\nsrc = 192.168.1.1 (rewritten)
SRV -[#43A047]-> GW : HTTP 200 OK
GW -[#43A047]-> C : HTTP 200 OK
note right of CAP : R5: ip && (tcp||udp||icmp) >= 10

== INBOUND BLOCK ==

SRV -[#E53935]> GW : SYN → 10.0.1.10:22
GW -[#E53935]>x GW : dropped (no DNAT rule)
note right of GW #FFCDD2 : inbound blocked by default

legend right
  PCAP on gateway (interface any) shows
  DORA with transaction ID correlation
  and source-address rewrite proving NAT.
  Inbound attempt has no reply in capture.
endlegend
@enduml
